{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5ce17eab-93e8-4236-8322-1f9c327885a5","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IDisposable, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected automatically via constructor in MSTest 3.x\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; } \n\n    private readonly HttpClient _client;\n\n    // Synchronous initialization via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization — implement IAsyncInit\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test setup work\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/warmup\");\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest() => Assert.IsNotNull(TestContext);\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest()\n    {\n        var response = await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(response.IsSuccessStatusCode);\n    }\n\n    // Sync cleanup\n    public void Dispose() => _client.Dispose();\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync() => await Task.CompletedTask;\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest 3.x:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is passed via constructor (no need for the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern).\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` for per-test, or `[ClassInitialize]` (static) for once-per-class.\n- **Cleanup** — implement `IDisposable` / `IAsyncDisposable` instead of `[TestCleanup]` if you prefer deterministic disposal.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d64ff9e3-3279-43e1-b712-ef17f81eddf6","outputTokens":463,"requestId":"9C44:113D23:16E2710:1997C18:69F864E9"},"id":"8a0f4b4e-2e0d-4331-9a9f-c0d562c9329d","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:20:50.290Z","parentId":"4607382a-896a-4a6c-826f-b39924686dac"}
